# {{APP_NAME}}

{{APP_DESCRIPTION}}

## Features

- Multi-track microphone recording (Web Audio API)
- Per-track volume mixing and playback
- WAV export of the mixed result
- Optional AI-assisted title/description generation via the Claude API (experimental —
  see "Known limitations" below)
- Fully offline capable (Service Worker)
- PWA (add to home screen)

## Installation

This app runs entirely in your browser. No server needed once built.

### On Desktop / Mobile
Open this repository with GitHub Pages enabled:
`https://{{REPO_OWNER}}.github.io/{{REPO_NAME}}/{{APP_DIR}}/`

- **Android Chrome**: Tap address bar → "Install" (or menu → "Install app")
- **iOS Safari**: Share button → "Add to Home Screen"

## How to Use

1. Gear icon (top right) → enter a Claude API key (only needed for AI processing)
2. "録音開始" (Start recording) → grant mic permission → record
3. Record multiple times to add tracks; adjust each track's volume
4. "再生" (Play) to preview the mixed result
5. "AI処理" (AI process) → optional title/description suggestions
6. "ダウンロード" (Download) → get a mixed WAV file

## Known limitations

- The AI-processing feature calls `api.anthropic.com` directly from the browser with a
  user-supplied API key stored in `localStorage`. This is likely to hit CORS
  restrictions in real deployments, and Claude does not natively transcribe or
  understand raw audio — treat this feature as experimental, not a reliable
  transcription pipeline.
- MP3 export is not implemented; only WAV.

## For Developers

Source lives in `{{APP_DIR}}-app/` (React + Vite + Tailwind), **not** deployed
directly. To make changes:

```bash
cd {{APP_DIR}}-app
npm install
npm run dev      # http://localhost:5173

# When ready to deploy:
npm run build    # builds straight into ../{{APP_DIR}}/
cd ..
git add {{APP_DIR}}-app {{APP_DIR}}
git commit -m "build: update {{APP_DIR}}"
git push
```

`npm run build` overwrites `{{APP_DIR}}/` entirely (`emptyOutDir: true`) — never hand-edit
files there.

## Technical Details

- **Framework**: React 18 + Vite + Tailwind CSS
- **Storage**: localStorage (API key only; recordings are in-memory per session)
- **Offline**: Service Worker caches the app shell; JS/CSS bundles cache on first load
- **Privacy**: Recordings never leave the device unless you use the AI-processing feature
